figgy.title: [Figgy/staging] Errno::E2BIG: Argument list too long when running mosaic generator

comments.body:
This is difficult to diagnose without access to the original dataset which appears to have been deleted. The error appears when Figgy attempts to pass too many raster urls into the mosaic generator process. I'm going to close this, and if we see it it again in production, we can work on it.

Running `getconf ARG_MAX` on figgy-staging2 returned a value of 2097152 bytes (2.1 MB).

Running `xargs --show-limits --no-run-if-empty </dev/null` returns:

```

Your environment variables take up 2176 bytes
POSIX upper limit on argument length (this system): 2092928
POSIX smallest allowable upper limit on argument length (all systems): 4096
Maximum length of command we could actually use: 2090752
Size of command buffer we are actually using: 131072
Maximum parallelism (--max-procs must be no greater): 2147483647
```
